(cl:comment "Dau's example of complex ligature handling in Peirce's Beta graphs")
(cl:comment "Logical form: ∃x(P(x) ∧ ¬Q(x))")
(cl:comment "Source: Dau (2006), Mathematical Logic with Diagrams, p. 112")

(cl:text
  (cl:imports "http://www.example.org/ontology/scholar-examples")
  
  (cl:comment "Existential quantification with negation: There exists something that is P but not Q")
  (exists (x)
    (and (P x) (not (Q x))))
)

